createFromSets

public static Delta createFromSets(Set<Triple> addedTriples,
                                   Set<Triple> deletedTriples)
Creates a new Delta object from two sets containing the added and deleted triples. Since a triple is always related to an owner model, the triples are first read into two models.

Parameters:
addedTriples - The added triples
deletedTriples - The deleted triples
Returns:
The delta created by two seta of triples

applyToModel

public static void applyToModel(Delta delta,
                                Model m)
Applies a delta to the given model. Removes from the model all the deleted triples of the delta and adds all the added triples of the delta.

Parameters:
delta - The delta that will be applied
m - The model on which the delta will be applied

areCompatible

public boolean areCompatible(Delta delta1,
                             Delta delta2)
Checks whether two deltas are compatible. Two deltas are compatible if the set of added and deleted triples are disjoint.

Parameters:
delta1 - The first delta
delta - The second delta
Returns:
true if the two given deltas are compatible else false

union

public static Delta union(Delta delta1,
                          Delta delta2)
Computes the union of the two given deltas. Creates a new delta that contains as the set of added triples the union of the added triples of the two deltas and as the set of deleted triples the union of the deleted triples of the two deltas.

Parameters:
delta1 - The first delta
delta2 - The second delta
Returns:
A new delta that is the union of the two deltas
